<h1>Research</h1>

{% set typeOrder = ["Book Chapter", "Peer Reviewed", "Other Published Work", "Country Report", "Technical Note", "PhD Dissertation", "Research Assistance"] %}
{% set typeLabels = {
  "Book Chapter": "Book chapters",
  "Peer Reviewed": "Peer reviewed",
  "Other Published Work": "Other published works",
  "Country Report": "Country reports",
  "Technical Note": "Technical notes",
  "PhD Dissertation": "PhD dissertation",
  "Research Assistance": "Research assistance"
} %}

{% for type in typeOrder %}
  {% set pubs = [] %}
  {% for pub in publications %}
    {% if pub.type == type %}
      {% set pubs = (pubs.push(pub), pubs) %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
  {% if pubs.length > 0 %}
  <div class="info-section">
    <h2 class="section-label">{{ typeLabels[type] }}</h2>
    {% for pub in pubs %}
    <div class="pub-entry">
      <div class="pub-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="pub-toggle-icon"></span>
        <span class="pub-title">
          {% if pub.url %}<a href="{{ pub.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener" onclick="event.stopPropagation()">{{ pub.title }}</a>{% else %}{{ pub.title }}{% endif %}
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="pub-details">
        <div class="pub-details-inner">
          {% if pub.authors %}<div class="pub-authors">With: {{ pub.authors }}</div>{% endif %}
          <div class="pub-venue">{{ pub.publication }}</div>
          {% if pub.abstract %}<div class="pub-description">{{ pub.abstract }}</div>{% endif %}
          {% if pub.extras %}<div class="pub-description"><em>{{ pub.extras }}</em></div>{% endif %}
          <div class="citation-box">
            <div class="citation-text" id="cite-{{ loop.index0 }}-{{ type | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}">{{ pub.citation }}</div>
            <div class="citation-buttons">
              <button class="citation-copy" data-cite-id="cite-{{ loop.index0 }}-{{ type | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}" data-format="plain" aria-label="Copy citation">Copy Citation</button>
              <button class="citation-copy" data-bibtex='{"authors":"{{ pub.citation.split(".")[0] | replace("'", "") }}","title":"{{ pub.title | replace("'", "") }}","year":"{{ pub.year }}","venue":"{{ pub.publication | replace("'", "") }}","url":"{{ pub.url or "" }}"}' data-format="bibtex" aria-label="Copy BibTeX">BibTeX</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}

<div class="divider">·</div>

<div class="info-section compact-section">
  <div class="info-grid info-grid-3col">
    <div class="info-block">
      <h2 class="section-label">Capacity development</h2>
      <p>As part of my work in the <a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/project/southmod-simulating-tax-and-benefit-policies-development-phase-3">SOUTHMOD</a> project at <a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/">UNU-WIDER</a>, I've delivered microsimulation workshops for various public and private institutions in Uganda (e.g., <a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/event/ugamod-retreat">2022</a>, <a href="https://unu.edu/training/second-ugamod-retreat-0">2023</a>), Rwanda (<a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/event/rwamod-training">2022</a>, <a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/event/second-rwamod-training">2023</a>) and Vietnam (<a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/event/vnmod-retreat">2022</a>, <a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/event/second-vnmod-retreat">2023</a>) and helped develop the <a href="https://learning.wider.unu.edu/group/2">SOUTHMOD online course</a>, launched in May 2024.</p>
      <p>I'm a mentor in the <a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/opportunity/visiting-phd-fellowship">UNU-WIDER PhD Fellowship Programme</a>, expert at the <a href="https://community.unesco.org/inclusivepolicylab/s/profile/005Sm00000EiUifIAF">UNESCO Inclusive Policy Lab</a>, and chair of the Working Group on AI at UNU-WIDER.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="info-block">
      <h2 class="section-label">Conference presentations</h2>
      <p>I've presented research at conferences in Tanzania, Uganda, the Netherlands, United States, Macau, Finland and various online seminars. See e.g.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://unu.edu/macau/aiconf2025">UNU Macau AI conference</a>, 2025</li>
        <li><a href="https://aimacau-2024.org/">UNU Macau AI conference</a>, 2024</li>
        <li>SOUTHMOD presentation at the LOTTE-Skatt conference, 2023</li>
        <li>The Futures of Global Social Policy Workshop, 2022</li>
        <li>Global Development Conference, 2022</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="info-block">
      <h2 class="section-label">Media and blogs</h2>
      <p>Here's a brief selection of blog posts and op-eds I've authored that are available online:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.wider.unu.edu/expert/jesse-lastunen?f%5B0%5D=content_type:Blog">UNU-WIDER blog posts (WIDERAngle)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://kehityslehti.fi/13233/index.html">Interview in Kehityslehti</a>, 2021</li>
        <li><a href="https://theconversation.com/efforts-to-protect-the-poor-during-covid-how-five-african-countries-fared-171131">Blog post, The Conversation</a>, 2021</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.project-syndicate.org/commentary/reforming-african-tax-and-social-protection-systems-after-covid19-by-jesse-lastunen-1-et-al-2021-12">Blog post, Project Syndicate</a>, 2021</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.hs.fi/paakirjoitukset/art-2000002748437.html">Op-ed, Helsingin Sanomat</a>, 2015</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Here's a <a href="https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/01/prompts-for-economists.html">Marginal Revolution post</a> of my 'AI for Economists' library, developed in 2024 (superseded by <a href="/ai-econ/">this resource section</a>).</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

